Phase 7 implementation note: `web/src/lib/engine-ingest-contract.ts` defines
the canonical versioned payload and HMAC signature contract for Python-engine
alerts. `POST /api/engine/alerts` verifies
`x-market-catalyst-timestamp` and `x-market-catalyst-signature`, rejects stale
requests outside a five-minute replay window, validates the payload with Zod,
and writes `NewsEvent`, `MarketReaction`, and `Alert` in one transaction through
`web/src/lib/engine-ingest-store.ts`. Duplicate runner cycles are blocked by
`idempotencyKey` and `sourceFingerprint`. `macro_web_ingest.py` builds the same
payload from `macro_live_signal_current.csv`, validates it locally, signs it,
and supports dry-run inspection before posting. Approved-alert fan-out now
creates per-subscriber delivery queue records for eligible users. Provider
dispatch from that queue remains pending for Phase 8.

