1.	ADMIN PURPOSE 
What to do:
Create a secure control center where app owners, staff, moderators, managers, and support teams can manage the entire application.
How to do it:
The admin panel should allow authorized users to view users, manage settings, review activity, control permissions, handle reports, monitor payments, manage content, and audit system behavior.
Expected output:
One dashboard that controls the app without needing direct database access.
==================================================
2.	ADMIN USER ROLES 
What to do:
Create different admin permission levels.
How to do it:
Use role-based access control.
Main roles:
SUPER ADMIN
Full access to everything.
Can create other admins.
Can change system settings.
Can delete or suspend accounts.
Can view logs and financial records.
ADMIN
Can manage users, content, reports, and daily operations.
Cannot change critical system settings unless allowed.
MANAGER
Can view reports, approve actions, and supervise staff.
Limited access to sensitive data.
SUPPORT STAFF
Can view user issues, tickets, account status, and basic user information.
Cannot delete users or change system rules.
MODERATOR
Can approve, reject, flag, hide, or remove content.
Can handle user reports.
FINANCE ADMIN
Can view payments, subscriptions, payouts, invoices, refunds, and revenue.
READ-ONLY ADMIN
Can view dashboards and reports only.
Cannot make changes.
